# Nesta's collective intelligence design playbook

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Overview
The Collective Intelligence Design Playbook is a guide that helps designers and facilitators create collective intelligence interventions.

## Purpose
To design and deliver collective intelligence projects by guiding users through the different stages of designing such an intervention.

## How it works
The playbook provides various canvases, decision trees, and other tools to help guide users through the process of creating a collective intelligence project. It requires a basic understanding of participatory methods and data innovation.

## Requirements
A basic understanding of participatory methods and data innovation is necessary to effectively use the Collective Intelligence Design Playbook.

## Reflections
The core concept of collective intelligence requires some experience with collaborative work and facilitation techniques.

## Related methods (if any)
Collective Intelligence

## Examples
NESTA's own project, Smarter Together, uses the Collective Intelligence Design Playbook as a tool for creating collective intelligence interventions.
